1
00:00:33,480 --> 00:00:35,360
Come on, you can do it.

2
00:00:38,720 --> 00:00:39,200
Bye.

3
00:00:39,200 --> 00:00:40,280
I'll pick you up tonight.

4
00:00:40,280 --> 00:00:40,640
Okay.

5
00:00:40,840 --> 00:00:41,200
Okay.

6
00:00:43,920 --> 00:00:45,880
Sir, your room is on the 9th floor.

7
00:00:47,520 --> 00:00:49,050
The elevator is over there.

8
00:00:49,080 --> 00:00:51,480
Our hotel has 350 rooms

9
00:00:51,480 --> 00:00:53,120
and a 1,000-square-meter conference hall.

10
00:00:53,120 --> 00:00:53,880
What's wrong?

11
00:00:53,880 --> 00:00:54,920
Where is my room?

12
00:00:55,880 --> 00:00:59,080
I booked a room two weeks ago. Give me my room.

13
00:00:59,080 --> 00:01:00,880
I booked a room two weeks ago.

14
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:04,239
Is there a problem with my reservation?

15
00:01:04,239 --> 00:01:06,320
Excuse me, sir. How can I help you?

16
00:01:06,520 --> 00:01:07,880
Can you speak English?

17
00:01:07,880 --> 00:01:08,880
A little bit.

18
00:01:08,880 --> 00:01:12,400
A little bit is fine. I just want to confirm. Please hurry.

19
00:01:16,760 --> 00:01:18,560
What is this lady's name?

20
00:01:19,880 --> 00:01:21,680
Her name

21
00:01:23,360 --> 00:01:24,400
is Liu Meijuan.

22
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:26,080
She just started working here a few days ago.

23
00:01:26,080 --> 00:01:27,410
Her name is Liu Meijuan.

24
00:01:27,960 --> 00:01:31,600
It seems Ms. Liu's professional skills are quite outstanding.

25
00:01:31,880 --> 00:01:35,320
It just so happens that our company has a lot of foreign business coming up.

26
00:01:35,320 --> 00:01:38,080
Let her be in charge of foreign liaisons from now on.

27
00:01:38,080 --> 00:01:39,720
Let me introduce you two.

28
00:01:39,920 --> 00:01:40,250
Okay.

29
00:01:41,360 --> 00:01:41,960
Meijuan.

30
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:47,600
Manager.

31
00:01:47,920 --> 00:01:51,960
This is our hotel's VIP guest, Mr. Li Xuebo.

32
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:53,560
Hello, Mr. Li.

33
00:01:53,560 --> 00:01:55,360
Miss Liu, is there something you need?

34
00:01:55,360 --> 00:01:56,000
Mr. Li

35
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:58,680
specifically asked you to receive his foreign clients from now on.

36
00:01:58,680 --> 00:01:59,720
Yunting Hotel.

37
00:02:00,320 --> 00:02:01,720
But I'm just a receptionist.

38
00:02:01,720 --> 00:02:03,920
It doesn't matter. From today on,

39
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:06,200
you'll be in charge of Mr. Li's business.

40
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:07,360
Yunting Hotel.

41
00:02:07,360 --> 00:02:08,639
Thank you, Mr. Li.

42
00:02:08,720 --> 00:02:09,600
Thank you, Manager.

43
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:10,530
You're welcome.

44
00:02:11,720 --> 00:02:12,880
I'm sorry.

45
00:02:15,280 --> 00:02:16,079
Sorry.

46
00:02:18,360 --> 00:02:19,880
How is work today?

47
00:02:19,880 --> 00:02:21,160
What time should I pick you up?

48
00:02:21,160 --> 00:02:22,280
I'm still at work.

49
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:25,079
Call me back later, okay?

50
00:02:26,760 --> 00:02:27,760
Sorry.

51
00:02:28,880 --> 00:02:30,010
What a coincidence.

52
00:02:30,880 --> 00:02:32,340
We have the same ringtone.

53
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:33,040
Yes.

54
00:02:34,200 --> 00:02:35,600
Do you like this song too?

55
00:02:35,880 --> 00:02:36,880
Yes.

56
00:02:37,120 --> 00:02:39,800
Liu, give Mr. Li your contact info.

57
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:42,800
Tell him to contact you directly if he needs anything.

58
00:02:51,160 --> 00:02:52,840
Come get your sugarcane!

59
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:54,480
Authentic local sugarcane.

60
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:57,040
Fifty cents a jin.

61
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:59,040
One yuan for three.

62
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:02,280
Sweet and juicy.

63
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:03,800
Bro, are you new here?

64
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:05,850
Is the sugarcane sweet?

65
00:03:05,960 --> 00:03:08,290
If it's not sweet, it's free. Have a taste.

66
00:03:09,560 --> 00:03:09,920
How is it?

67
00:03:09,920 --> 00:03:10,980
It is really sweet.

68
00:03:14,040 --> 00:03:14,840
Fifty cents.

69
00:03:19,360 --> 00:03:20,360
You don't know me?

70
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:23,680
But you know Xiaofei, right?

71
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:26,100
You don't get to call him Xiaofei.

72
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:30,360
Brother Fei. If you dare to charge me,

73
00:03:31,079 --> 00:03:33,680
don't ever set up your stall here again, got it?

74
00:03:36,640 --> 00:03:37,280
Got it.

75
00:03:37,280 --> 00:03:38,520
Louder!

76
00:03:40,040 --> 00:03:40,600
Got it!

77
00:03:40,600 --> 00:03:42,320
Then go sell your sugarcane.

78
00:03:54,640 --> 00:03:56,440
Boss, how much is the sugarcane?

79
00:03:56,920 --> 00:03:58,720
Fifty cents a stalk,

80
00:03:58,840 --> 00:03:59,900
three for a dollar.

81
00:04:00,120 --> 00:04:01,450
Try it. It's very sweet.

82
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:03,100
It doesn't look sweet.

83
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:05,210
Just try it. Free if it's not sweet.

84
00:04:21,680 --> 00:04:24,920
Sugarcane for sale, fifty cents a jin.

85
00:04:25,120 --> 00:04:26,640
Sweet and juicy!

86
00:04:29,240 --> 00:04:32,720
Your health has improved a lot since you transferred to a civilian post.

87
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:35,240
It's mainly because Yinuo's mental state is better now.

88
00:04:35,240 --> 00:04:36,700
So I'm in a better mood too.

89
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:38,600
I need to tell you something.

90
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:41,060
Our department hasn't been too busy lately.

91
00:04:41,320 --> 00:04:43,320
There's an urgent matter at home.

92
00:04:43,320 --> 00:04:45,240
I need to go back right away.

93
00:04:45,840 --> 00:04:47,440
I'm leaving right away.

94
00:04:47,840 --> 00:04:49,240
Here are my house keys.

95
00:04:49,440 --> 00:04:50,280
I'll leave them with you for the week.

96
00:04:50,280 --> 00:04:52,400
Please thank your wife for me.

97
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:53,520
Alright.

98
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:55,960
I'll approve your leave.

99
00:04:55,960 --> 00:04:59,520
But take care of your health after you get home.

100
00:04:59,520 --> 00:05:00,240
Take your medicine on time.

101
00:05:00,240 --> 00:05:01,700
And get regular checkups.

102
00:05:01,920 --> 00:05:02,920
Okay.

103
00:05:04,320 --> 00:05:05,920
You nag more as you get older.

104
00:05:06,760 --> 00:05:07,840
Get back to work.

105
00:05:08,080 --> 00:05:10,240
Are you my boss, or am I yours?

106
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:14,520
You look busy.

107
00:05:24,440 --> 00:05:25,680
He's taking another long vacation.

108
00:05:25,680 --> 00:05:27,280
Another long vacation?

109
00:05:27,440 --> 00:05:29,640
Clerical jobs have more holidays.

110
00:05:30,400 --> 00:05:32,200
What can I do if he applied for it?

111
00:05:33,760 --> 00:05:35,890
I knew he wasn't a responsible person.

112
00:05:43,680 --> 00:05:44,480
Lin Wei.

113
00:05:45,159 --> 00:05:47,040
I'm not speaking up for Ma,

114
00:05:47,240 --> 00:05:49,960
but there's something you must know.

115
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:53,800
Before going to Chudong, you guaranteed

116
00:05:54,040 --> 00:05:57,280
you'd take all the responsibility.

117
00:05:57,360 --> 00:05:58,440
But then it went over the time limit.

118
00:05:58,440 --> 00:06:00,440
The higher-ups have looked into it.

119
00:06:00,840 --> 00:06:03,000
It was Ma who took the blame for you.

120
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:06,060
Otherwise, the one doing clerical work wouldn't be Ma.

121
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:08,220
It would be you.

122
00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:13,840
Captain Li, your report is here.

123
00:06:24,040 --> 00:06:24,880
Mr. Li,

124
00:06:25,160 --> 00:06:27,890
this is the largest exhibition hall we have here.

125
00:06:28,080 --> 00:06:30,600
It can hold about 300 people.

126
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:32,690
It should be enough for your event.

127
00:06:32,760 --> 00:06:34,690
No problem. Let's go with this one.

128
00:06:35,159 --> 00:06:37,480
Ms. Liu, thank you for taking the time

129
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:38,960
to show me around the exhibition halls all day.

130
00:06:38,960 --> 00:06:40,560
It's almost time for dinner.

131
00:06:40,880 --> 00:06:42,600
Let's see if we can

132
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:44,080
grab a quick bite together.

133
00:06:44,080 --> 00:06:45,409
We can talk while we eat.

134
00:06:46,880 --> 00:06:48,800
Sure. Let's

135
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:50,360
go.

136
00:06:54,560 --> 00:06:56,760
Ms. Liu, look,

137
00:06:57,080 --> 00:06:58,560
we're pretty well acquainted now.

138
00:06:58,560 --> 00:07:00,490
Let me call you Meijuan from now on.

139
00:07:01,160 --> 00:07:01,960
Is that okay?

140
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:03,560
Yes, that's fine, Mr. Li.

141
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:05,420
You can call me whatever you want.

142
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:07,660
Look, since I'm calling you Meijuan,

143
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:09,360
you should just call me Xuebo.

144
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:11,400
It makes us seem less like strangers.

145
00:07:11,400 --> 00:07:12,840
Okay.

146
00:07:15,080 --> 00:07:15,960
When we first met,

147
00:07:15,960 --> 00:07:19,220
I heard the manager say you haven't been working here long.

148
00:07:19,760 --> 00:07:20,640
Are you a local?

149
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:23,040
I'm not a local.

150
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:25,060
I've been working here for a year.

151
00:07:27,080 --> 00:07:28,410
What about before that?

152
00:07:29,440 --> 00:07:31,160
I used to work in my hometown.

153
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:33,290
What about you? Are you a local?

154
00:07:33,360 --> 00:07:34,360
I am a local.

155
00:07:34,440 --> 00:07:36,600
But I just came back recently too.

156
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:16,960
I'm sorry. I used to...

157
00:08:24,520 --> 00:08:25,520
It's fine, Hua.

158
00:08:26,720 --> 00:08:29,440
You might just be too tired lately.

159
00:08:30,920 --> 00:08:32,120
Working too hard.

160
00:08:33,320 --> 00:08:38,200
Yeah, stocking up has been a bit tiring lately.

161
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:42,440
How about we try again tomorrow?

162
00:08:44,760 --> 00:08:46,890
Better take care of your health first.

163
00:08:47,640 --> 00:08:48,840
Health is important.

164
00:09:17,120 --> 00:09:17,520
Hello.

165
00:09:17,920 --> 00:09:18,480
Meijuan.

166
00:09:18,880 --> 00:09:21,320
We might have to reschedule our lunch appointment.

167
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:22,680
Something came up at the company.

168
00:09:22,680 --> 00:09:23,880
I have to go handle it.

169
00:09:24,160 --> 00:09:26,220
Let's move our meal to the afternoon.

170
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:27,760
I've already booked the restaurant.

171
00:09:27,760 --> 00:09:28,560
See you then.

172
00:09:29,520 --> 00:09:30,640
Okay.

173
00:09:31,040 --> 00:09:32,240
Wait for my good news.

174
00:09:32,640 --> 00:09:33,440
Yeah.

175
00:09:55,360 --> 00:09:57,200
Who was that just now?

176
00:09:58,560 --> 00:09:59,440
A hotel client.

177
00:10:02,400 --> 00:10:05,040
Then I'll pick you up from work tonight.

178
00:10:06,240 --> 00:10:06,800
No need.

179
00:10:06,800 --> 00:10:08,530
I'm working overtime tonight.

180
00:10:08,560 --> 00:10:11,490
No. It's too dangerous for you to walk alone at night.

181
00:10:11,560 --> 00:10:12,560
Let me pick you up.

182
00:10:14,040 --> 00:10:14,840
Really, no need.

183
00:10:14,840 --> 00:10:16,720
I don't know how late I'll be working.

184
00:10:16,720 --> 00:10:18,040
You work so hard every day.

185
00:10:18,040 --> 00:10:19,680
Just go home and go to bed early.

186
00:10:19,680 --> 00:10:20,480
It's fine.

187
00:10:21,080 --> 00:10:22,080
All right.
